9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1299, L.D. 1940, “An Act to Revise the
10 Growth Management Program Laws”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 1. 30-A MRSA §4301, sub-§1, as corrected by RR 2017, c. 1, §22, is repealed
13 and the following enacted in its place:
14 1. Affordable housing. "Affordable housing" means a decent, safe and sanitary
15 dwelling as follows:
16 F. Rental housing that a household whose income does not exceed 80% of the median
17 income for the area as defined by the United States Department of Housing and Urban
18 Development under the United States Housing Act of 1937, Public Law 75-412, 50
19 Stat. 888, Section 8, as amended, can afford without spending more than 30% of the
20 household's monthly income on housing costs; and
21 G. With respect to housing that is owned, housing that a household whose income does
22 not exceed 120% of the median income for the area as defined by the United States
23 Department of Housing and Urban Development under the United States Housing Act
24 of 1937, Public Law 75-412, 50 Stat. 888, Section 8, as amended, can afford without
25 spending more than 30% of the household's monthly income on housing costs.
26 Sec. 2. 30-A MRSA §4301, sub-§1-A, as enacted by PL 2005, c. 244, §1, is
27 amended to read:
28 1-A. Cluster development. "Cluster development" means a form of development that
29 allows a subdivision design in which individual lot sizes and setbacks are reduced in
30 exchange for the creation of common open space and recreation areas, the preservation of
31 environmentally sensitive areas, agriculture and silviculture and the reduction in the size
32 of road and utility systems.
33 Sec. 3. 30-A MRSA §4301, sub-§12-A is enacted to read:
34 12-A. Placetype. "Placetype" means a definable geographic settlement pattern
35 identifiable by the type of activities that occur there and by a set of characteristics related
